Overview of verb groom

The verb groom has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) prepare, groom, train -- (educate for a future role or function; "He is grooming his son to become his successor"; "The prince was prepared to become King one day"; "They trained him to be a warrior")
